
- Object -> Function -> Modified Object -> Function -> Modified Object ...
- Imperative vs. Declarative. HOW vs WHAT
Functional programming is like describing your problem to a mathematician.
Imperative programming is like giving instructions to an idiot.


- Avoiding mutable state
- Side effect free functions
- Referential transparency
- First-Class citizens - Stored in variables, passed as a function, returned from functions 
- Higher-Order Functions
- Lambdas and Closures
- Lazy Evaluation
- Recursion

